parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of power, coolant leakage, and potentially catastrophic engine damage, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine overheating
coolant leakage
loss of power
temperature spikes
engine oil in coolant reservoir
coolant spewing onto engine
and unexpected bubbling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking of the engine block can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of power, coolant leakage, and potentially catastrophic engine damage, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine overheating
coolant leakage
loss of power
temperature spikes
and repeated instances of overheating requiring immediate pullovers in dangerous traffic situations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crank/cam/oil pan silicone seals can cause the engine to leak oil, leading to premature wear and potentially catastrophic engine damage, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine oil leakage
premature wear of engine components
and failure of the timing belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of power, coolant leakage, and potentially catastrophic engine damage, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine overheating
coolant leakage
loss of power
and failure of the timing chain.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine stalling intermittently during normal operation
loss of power
and failure of the sensor valve and computer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also lead to costly repairs, as seen in complaint 10121358.
symptoms: The engine does not hold the car back when going down hills
the transmission does not shift into top gear on the freeway
the vehicle hesitates or shakes
the transmission slips out of gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spontaneous shift into neutral can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It is a major safety issue, as seen in complaint 740350.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into neutral spontaneously
the vehicle loses power and control
the transmission slips out of gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear differential failure can cause the vehicle to catch fire, leading to accidents or property damage. It can also lead to costly repairs, as seen in complaint 10171269.
symptoms: The rear differential overheats
the vehicle catches fire
the spare tire is used without plugging in the fuse
which can cause the emergency light to illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Speedometer and RPM issues can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also lead to costly repairs, as seen in complaint 860792.
symptoms: The speedometer does not work correctly
the RPM slows down
the vehicle jerks forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Driveshaft imbalance can cause the vehicle to vibrate, leading to loss of control and accidents. It can also lead to costly repairs, as seen in complaint 781211.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates at high speeds
the driveshaft is not properly balanced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure due to Moisture in Brake Hose
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, or accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake pedal is stiff with little to no travel distance
the vehicle hydroplanes or spins out while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Brake System Failure in Cold Temperatures
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power brake system in cold temperatures can cause the brake pedal to remain high and stiff, making it difficult to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal remains high and stiff with little to no travel distance
the brake pedal travels normally after warming up or sharply depressing the pedal several times
the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal to engage can cause the vehicle to continue accelerating while the brake pedal is pressed, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle continues to accelerate while standing on the brake pedal
the brake pedal goes to the floor and the vehicle does not stop.
